48... Qxa6 { In fact, not the correct capture. } (48... Rxa6! $10 { would have kept the evaluation level. }) 49. Rd8+! (49. Qc8+?? { blunders the queen } 49... Qxc8 $19) 49... Kh7 50. Rh8+! { Now the mating net has been cast. } (50. Qh3+?? { does not work because of } 50... Rh6! $19 51. Qf5+ Qg6! { and White is down a pawn and even facing an attack if they don't trade queens. }) (50. Qh8+?? $10 Kg6 { There's no clear way for White to win something, anything — not the rook, not the queen, not any of the pawns. White has no better than perpetual. } 51. Qg8+ Kf6 52. Qh8+ $10) 50... Kg6 51. Rg8+! (51. Qc2+?? $10 f5 $10 { and White has no clear continuation to win, so, again, they have to give perpetual (eventually). }) 51... Kf5 52. Qf3+! { Black's king is slowly being constricted by White's pieces, and eventually the queen-rook tandem will either force checkmate or heavy material loss for Black. } (52. Qc2+?? $10 { Once more doesn't work }) 52... Ke6 53. Re8+! { Not the only winning move, but the fastest. } (53. Qe3+ { Also wins, but let's do better }) (53. Rf8 { Also wins, but let's do better }) (53. Qe4+ { Also wins, but let's do better }) 53... Kd6 { Anything wins now; let's just check out one sample line. } (53... Kd7 54. Qxf7+) 54. Qf6+ Kc5 55. Qxg5+ (55. Qe5+ { Also wins, but let's do better }) (55. Qf5+ { Also wins, but let's do better }) (55. Qc3+ { Also wins, but let's do better }) (55. Re5+ { Also wins, but let's do better }) (55. Qf2+ { Also wins, but let's do better }) 55... Kc6 56. Qf6+ Kc5 57. Re5+ Kd4 58. Qf4+ Kd3 59. Qe3# 1-0


