39... axb1=Q+ { Looks natural, but now, surprisingly, even with Black to move, Black has no useful moves that help them parry White's threats. } (39... Qxb7 $10 { would have maintained the balance. }) 40. Rxb1 exf5 41. Qg7+! (41. Qh6+?? $19 { allows Black's king to escape as White does not have contact with the f7-pawn anymore, meaning there's no Qxf7+ in some critical lines. } 41... Ke8 42. Qh8+ Kd7 $19 { White is down a rook for a pawn and has no attack. }) 41... Ke8 { Try to not let the Black king escape. } 42. Rb6!! { The king's path to e6 as well as c6 is no longer possible, and Black's Rc6 is also blocked. There are a lot of complications ahead, so we'll show just one sample line to show how play might continue. } { [%csl Gc6][%cal Ge8d7,Gd7e6] } 42... Ne6 43. Qg8+ Nf8 44. e6 fxe6 45. Bg7 Qc7 46. Rxe6+ Kd7 47. Qf7+ Kc8 48. Re8+ Kb7 49. Re7 { And White picks up the queen } 1-0


