41... Rf8 { To retreat or not to retreat? } 42. Qxf8+! { Of course! White at least gets an imbalanced position out of this move, and with Be5 and Rf7 as ideas, probably more than that. } 42... Bxf8 43. Rxf8+ Kh7 { Two moves win here, but one is easier, and prettier, than the other. } 44. Bf1! { An important rerouting, threatening Bd3+, followed by Be5 ideas with mate soon to follow. } (44. Rf7!? $18 Qa8 45. Be5 Qg8 { and White can't take on g7 because that would lead to an equal endgame, so to win, White must start pushing their pawn, carefully, or play the mainline idea on move 44, so why not play the idea immediately? }) (44. Be5?? Qe7 { [%csl Ge6,Gf8] } 45. Rf7 Qg5 $10 { The endgame with Rxg7+ is just equal, and now that Black's queen in the game, it's difficult to stop perpetual. }) 44... Bb5 { Stopping Bd3. We could win in different ways here, but let's use an idea we've already discussed. } 45. Rf7! $18 { [%cal Ge6e7,Gg3e5] } (45. Bxb5 Qxb5 46. e7 { Also wins easily, and fadter than 45. Rf7, in fact. }) (45. Be5 { Also wins } { [%cal Gf8f7] }) 1-0


