{ There's one move you'd love to play. Can you make it work? }
20... c4!! { Threatening Nd3, the move you'd love to play. And, well, the knight is not hanging! } { [%clk 0:07:12] } (20... Nd5?? 21. Qxd5) (20... Nc6?? $10 { Actually also sets up a queen trap, but White doesn't have to fall into it and could just play normally. A lot of moves are equal in this position. } 21. Qd5!? $10 (21. Qc2! $10) 21... Re6! 22. Qxc6!? $10 { Falling into the trap, but White gets enough material for the queen. } (22. dxc5! $10 dxc5 23. Qxd8+ Rxd8 $10 24. Bxc5 Rxe1+ 25. Nxe1 Bxc5 26. Rxc5 Nd4 $10 { If anything, Black is better. }) 22... d5 23. Qxe6 fxe6 24. dxc5 Bc7 $10 { White has sufficient compensation for the queen. }) 21. Qxb4 { What was the point of the previous move? } { [%clk 0:05:58] } 21... Ba5! { Blocking b3, of course! Goodbye to her majesty. } { [%clk 0:07:20] } 22. Bg5 { A tricky response tried in the game. } { [%clk 0:05:14] } 22... hxg5! { The queen is still trapped, but White picks up Black's rook. } { [%clk 0:07:22] } (22... Bxb4! { Also wins, though, so 22. Bg5 is not much of a trick! } 23. Bxd8 Bxe1 24. Bc7 Rc8 25. Bxd6 Ba5) (22... Qb6!? { Even wins, but wastes a tempo. }) (22... Rxe1+? { May still be winning, but why not play simpler chess? } 23. Qxe1 Qxg5! { A clever desperado } 24. Nxg5 Bxe1 25. Rxe1 hxg5 $19 { and the endgame should be winning. Again, though, completely unnecessary! }) (22... f6?! { Still wins, and creates a cute pawn structure! } { [%cal Ga5b4] }) 23. Rxe4 { [%clk 0:04:42] } 23... Bxb4 { [%clk 0:07:29] } 24. axb4 { Black has too much material and the conversion should not be difficult at all. } { [%clk 0:04:51] } 0-1


