25... Bxc4 { Imagine the positon after 25...Qxc4, which would in fact be winning for Black. Can you tell why 25...Bxc4 is wrong? } (25... Qxc4! $19 { just wins. }) 26. Rd8+!! { Distracting the rook from attacking c2! } (26. Qxh6?? $19 { Now we see why it's important to deflect the rook away from c2. } 26... Bxa2+ 27. Ka1 (27. Kc1 Qxc2#) 27... Bb3+ 28. Kb1 Qa2+ 29. Kc1 Rxc2#) (26. a3?? Nc3+ 27. Bxc3 Qxa3 28. Bb2 Ba2+ 29. Kc1 Qxe3+ 30. Rd2 Bb3 $19 { Black's attack is just too strong. }) 26... Rxd8 27. Qxh6! { [%csl Gg7,Gh8] } 27... f6! { Aronian finds the most annoying defense, but Black remains lost. } (27... Bxa2+ 28. Kc1! { and White is perfectly safe. }) 28. Rh1! (28. Qxg6+?? { Black is up a piece, so if we can't find anything clear, we're lost. } 28... Kf8! 29. Rh1 Bxa2+ { Why not? Playing 29...Ke7 immediately, getting the king safe, also wins. } 30. Kc1 Ke7!! 31. Rh7+ Kd6 { The Black king is safe and White is just down a piece. }) 28... Kf7 29. Qh7+ Ke8 30. Qg7!! { Crucial, not allowing the king to escape. } 30... Rd1+! { giving up the rook to stay in the game, but White is just material up now and still has an attack. } 31. Rxd1! $18 1-0


