47. Qxd5 { It looks like White is setting up a powerful tactic, with promotion and just having a winning material advantage. It looks like Black can try to play on the light squares, though. Can you find the precise continuation? } 47... Qxd5 { Of course, what else? } 48. b7 Qf3!! $19 { Setting up the correct battery! It turns out White has no way to defend against Black's threats. Let's try out some more moves. } { [%cal Gf5e4] } (48... Be4?? $10 { was tried in the game, leading only to a draw after } 49. b8=Q Qd1 50. Rg2 Bxg2 51. Kxg2 Qe2+ $10 { with eprpetual }) 49. b8=Q Be4! 50. g4! { A tough defense } 50... Qh1+ { Of course, what else? } 51. Kg3 Qg1+ 52. Kh3 (52. Rg2 Qxg2#) 52... h5!! { The key winning idea, setting up Bf5+, hxg4+, and Qg4+ ideas. } 53. Qc8 (53. f5 hxg4#) 53... Qh1+! { There are a few more ways to win now, but this should be among the simplest. } 54. Kg3 (54. Rh2 Qf3#) 54... Qf3+ 55. Kh2 hxg4 $19 { With g3 being the key idea to corral White's king. } { [%cal Gf3h3,Gg4g3] } 56. f5 g3+ 57. Kh3 (57. Bxg3 Qh1#) (57. Kg1 Qh1#) 57... g2+ 58. Kh2 Qg4! { Setting up decisive promotion threats } (58... Qf1! { Also wins, but is less accurate. }) 59. Bg3 (59. Rb1 g1=Q+ 60. Rxg1 Qxh4#) 59... g1=Q+! 60. Kxg1 Qxg3+ 61. Kf1 (61. Rg2 Qxg2#) 61... Bd3+ 62. Re2 Qf3+ 63. Kg1 Bxe2 $19 (63... Qxe2 { Also wins }) 1/2-1/2


