25. Qg4!! { A stunning move, and the only winning one. White is threatening Nf6+, with a quick mate after gxf6. If Kh8, Qh5 with Qxh7# ideas would come. Black can try to defend, but White has a crushing response to every possible Black move. } { [%clk 0:06:07] } 25... Bc8 { Forces White to find } { [%clk 0:02:27] } (25... Be5!? 26. Nf6+ Kh8 (26... Bxf6 27. gxf6 g6 28. Qf4 { [%cal Gf4h6] }) 27. Nxe8 Rxe8 28. Qd7 Rb8 29. Bxe5 Nxe5 30. Qd6 $18) (25... Ne5!? 26. Nf6+!! gxf6 27. Qf5!! { With similar ideas as 27. Qh5 in the mainline continuation. } (27. Qh5?? Ng6! $19) 27... Ng6 28. Qxa5 $18) (25... Re6 26. Nf6+ { is similar to the other lines. }) 26. Nf6+! { [%clk 0:05:16] } 26... gxf6 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 27. Qh5! { [%cal Gg5f6] [%clk 0:05:26] } (27. gxf6+?? { Don't fall for it! } 27... Bxg4 $19) 27... Bxh3 { [%clk 0:00:17] } 28. gxf6+ { [%clk 0:05:34] } 28... Kh8 { [%clk 0:00:24] } 29. Qxf7!! { [%cal Gf7g7] [%clk 0:05:43] } (29. Rg7?? Qxh5 $19) (29. Qh6! { is also good, but not as simple. } 29... Rg8 30. Rg7 Qf5 31. Rdg1 Rgf8 32. R7g5 $18 { [%cal Gh6g7] }) (29. Rg5! $18 { Also wins, but just wins material, Black's queen in all likelihood, and not the game immediately. }) 29... Rg8 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 30. Qxg8+!! { [%clk 0:05:50] } (30. Rg7 $18 { Also wins, but is much slower }) 30... Rxg8 31. f7+ Rg7 32. Bxg7# 1-0


